    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/651</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-12T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 13, 3.16 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>977. I have been able to get into telephone communication with Torneå and I am
                    informed that according to report current there <persName corresp="#p_KAF1"
                        >Kerensky</persName> is in control of Russian telegraphs; that telegrams
                    from southern Russia report country is controlled by Cossacks working under
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAF1">Kerensky</persName>; that the Bolshevik troops
                    badly beaten at Tsarskoe Selo and retired to Petrograd where they are quartered
                    in certain section of the city; that the. Allied missions in Petrograd are now
                    in connection with <persName corresp="#p_KAF1">Kerensky</persName> who has
                    announced Government centers at Moscow, Novocherkassk; that Generals <persName
                        corresp="#p_KGLG1">Kornilov</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KGAM1"
                        >Kaledin</persName> have called upon every one to oppose Bolsheviks.
                    According to passengers arriving at Torneå to-day from Petrograd, newspapers are
                    reappearing in Petrograd all announcing defeat of Bolsheviks; that there has
                    been considerable fighting on Nevski Prospekt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
